ARTiFACTS is configured to work seamlessly within the research ecosystem ARTiFACTS Bitbucket Mendeley Zotero Google Drive OneDrive GitLab GitHub orcID DropBox Amazon Web Services How are researchers using ARTiFACTS? To secure their artifacts to the blockchain, protect their IP, grow their reputation and collaboration networks To draw upon the ARTiFACTS index of citations to and published research To interoperate with their commonly used research tools, software and information systems Enterprise and community beneficiaries Publishers identify emerging talent, disciplines and enrich value of their content Funding organisations track outputs and impact Universities and research organisations monitor, benchmark and report performance Corporate R&D gains signal intelligence and access to experts At its heart, ARTiFACTS maintains a distributed ledger and transaction engine that records a permanent, valid, and immutable chain of records for all scientific and academic research â€˜transactionsâ€™ including citing (also known as attribution) transactions recorded onto the The ability to capture citing transactions is a unique and powerful requirement of scientific and academic This citation ability differentiates ARTiFACTS from general media ARTiFACTSâ€™ proprietary (patent pending) ability to authoritatively and rigorously manage citations, artifact linkages, and ownership or is unprecedented relative to current indexing, archiving, and researcher community What are the benefits of using ARTiFACTS?
